@startuml financial_targets
!theme plain
skinparam backgroundColor #FEFEFE
skinparam defaultFontSize 12
skinparam titleFontSize 18

title Financial Targets Dashboard (0–35)\nCustodial account is a teaching tool, not just a savings vehicle.\nDon't wait until they have money to teach them about money.

map "Birth" as ft0 {
  Target => 529 opened + UTMA/UGMA custodial brokerage
  Brain => Parent-managed; child unaware
}

map "Age 5–7" as ft5 {
  Target => Savings jar (Spend/Save/Invest) + connect brands to businesses
  Brain => Concrete thinking; habit formation window
}

map "Age 8–10" as ft10 {
  Target => Compound interest + show account statements + graph growth
  Brain => Cause/effect, basic math
}

map "Age 11–13" as ft11 {
  Target => Stock=ownership, Bond=loan, Index=basket; paper trading
  Brain => Abstract thinking emerging
}

map "Age 14–16" as ft14 {
  Target => Sector research + pick stocks together + Roth IRA eligible
  Brain => Future-outcome reasoning; reward circuitry developing
}

map "Age 16–18" as ft16 {
  Target => Portfolio allocation, diversification, DCA, tax implications
  Brain => Formal operational thinking; limbic still dominant
}

map "Age 18–25" as ft18 {
  Target => Roth strategy, market cycles, behavioral finance
  Brain => PFC developing; judgment incomplete
}

map "Age 25–30" as ft25 {
  Target => Positive net worth + tax-loss harvesting + real estate
  Brain => Male PFC maturing; judgment becoming reliable
}

map "Age 30–35" as ft35 {
  Target => Financial independence trajectory + generational wealth
  Brain => Full executive function; 5–10 years of validated decisions
}

ft0 -down-> ft5
ft5 -down-> ft10
ft10 -down-> ft11
ft11 -down-> ft14
ft14 -down-> ft16
ft16 -down-> ft18
ft18 -down-> ft25
ft25 -down-> ft35

note right of ft0
  UTMA (Virginia): custodian
  until age 21. No earned
  income required. Opens
  the door to teach investing
  from the earliest age.
end note

note right of ft14
  Custodial Roth IRA requires
  earned income (W-2 or
  legitimate self-employment).
  Contribution limit = lesser of
  $7,000 or total earned income.
end note

note right of ft18
  PFC still developing — high
  vulnerability to behavioral
  finance errors (FOMO, panic
  selling). Teach BEFORE they
  experience their first downturn.
end note

note bottom of ft35
  Key principle: A $100 custodial
  account the child watches and
  discusses is worth more educationally
  than a $50,000 529 they never
  think about.
end note

@enduml
